## Interface: 20505
## Title: LibCodex-1.0
## Notes: A reusable static-catalog library for WoW addons. Tracks NPCs, items, spells, talents, quests, zones, flight points, currencies, reputations, crafts, achievements, pets, mounts, etc. Hybrid load model: bundled seed + runtime growth. Consumers embed via ## libs and call LibStub("LibCodex-1.0").
## Author: ChronicTinkerer
## Version: 6
## SavedVariables: LibCodexDB
## LoadOnDemand: 0
## X-Curse-Project-ID: 1532131
## X-License: MIT
# NOTE: X-Wago-ID and X-WoWI-ID intentionally omitted on this first TBC
#       Anniversary ship. The BigWigs packager only uploads to sites
#       whose project ID is present in the TOC, so the TBC zip will
#       publish to CurseForge only. Add the two X-* lines once the
#       flavor is validated.
# Interface 20505 verified against .build.info (Version 2.5.5.67157)
# on 2026-05-05.
# NOTE: This TOC's data is sourced from wago.tools branch "wow_anniversary"
#       via tools/import-wago.py --flavor tbc, augmented by cmangos-tbc
#       SQL via tools/import-emulator-sql.py --flavor tbc.

# ----- Vendored LibStub (only loaded when LibCodex runs as a standalone addon
#       for development/testing; in production the consumer addon supplies its
#       own LibStub via embeds and this is a no-op since LibStub is idempotent)
embeds\LibStub\LibStub.lua

# ----- Vendored LibEditMode. Lets the Dashboard window
#       register with Blizzard's Edit Mode so users can move it via the
#       native Edit Mode UI. Soft-optional in the Dashboard code: if the
#       library isn't present, the dashboard still works as a draggable
#       frame, just without Edit Mode integration.
Libs\LibEditMode\LibEditMode.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\pools.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\button.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\checkbox.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\dialog.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\divider.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\dropdown.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\expander.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\extension.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\slider.lua
Libs\LibEditMode\widgets\colorpicker.lua

